The watchdog agency recalled 359 products, ranging from ready-made-meals to a popular brand of instant noodles, after finding traces of the illegal dye Sudan I. Sudan I, a potentially cancer- causing colorant, is the latest target for China's product quality watchdogs after the disclosure that the red dye has tainted hundreds of food items in Britain.
Meanwhile the European Commission, reporting the results of a two-day meeting on the British scare, revealed that the batch of potentially cancer-causing Sudan I dye at the root of the concern came from India.
